1
00:00:00,408 --> 00:00:03,061
<i>The Library!
So big it doesn't need a name.</i>

2
00:00:03,161 --> 00:00:05,450
Someone's got in.
Someone's in my library.

3
00:00:05,550 --> 00:00:07,265
4,022 saved.

4
00:00:07,465 --> 00:00:08,485
No survivors.

5
00:00:08,585 --> 00:00:11,111
- Others are coming.
- What... others?

6
00:00:16,853 --> 00:00:19,507
Professor River Song, archaeologist.

7
00:00:19,607 --> 00:00:21,138
You've seen me before, then?

8
00:00:21,301 --> 00:00:25,613
The real world is a lie,
and your nightmares are real.

9
00:00:26,755 --> 00:00:28,932
- What's CAL?!
- The Library is real.

10
00:00:29,214 --> 00:00:33,157
There are people trapped in there,
people who need to be saved.

11
00:00:33,526 --> 00:00:35,497
There's a neural relay
in the communicator.

12
00:00:35,597 --> 00:00:37,360
<i>Sometimes it can hold an impression</i>

13
00:00:37,460 --> 00:00:40,038
<i>of a living consciousness
for a short time after death.</i>

14
00:00:40,138 --> 00:00:43,532
The shadows are moving again.
Only you can save them.

15
00:00:43,632 --> 00:00:46,190
The piranhas of the air,
the Vashta Nerada.

16
00:00:49,180 --> 00:00:50,920
Donna Noble has been saved.

17
00:00:51,418 --> 00:00:53,301
Donna Noble has been saved.

18
00:00:53,401 --> 00:00:56,440
<i>- Who turned out the lights?
- Donna Noble has left the Library.</i>

19
00:00:56,911 --> 00:00:59,169
<i>Donna Noble has been saved.
Who turned out the lights?</i>

20
00:00:59,269 --> 00:01:03,120
Donna Noble has left the Library.
Donna Noble has been saved.

21
00:01:03,220 --> 00:01:06,520
<i>- Who turned out the lights?
- Donna Noble has left the Library.</i>

22
